#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:1
msgid "RoPA Records"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:3
msgid ""
"The RoPA Records feature lets Product Owners author and maintain a **Record "
"of Processing Activities** (RoPA) for every deployed process bundle, "
"fulfilling the mandatory GDPR Article 30 obligation for government "
"processing activities. Records are stored in PostgreSQL, linked to their "
"BPMN process via `ronl:ropaRef`, and published to a public-facing website "
"isolated from the LDE stack."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:12
msgid "Two-panel layout"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:14
msgid ""
"The RoPA Records view follows the same two-panel convention as the Form "
"Editor:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:16
msgid ""
"**Left panel** — Record list. All RoPA records grouped as shell processes "
"first, subprocesses second, each with a DRAFT / ACTIVE / ARCHIVED status "
"badge and a delete control."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:17
msgid ""
"**Right panel** — Record editor. Four tabs covering the full GDPR Art. 30 "
"data model, BPMN linkage, and lifecycle management."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:21
msgid "Record list"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:23
msgid ""
"Each entry in the list shows the record title, the `bpmnProcessId` it "
"covers, and its current status. Shell records are top-level entries; "
"subprocess records are indented beneath their parent shell with a tree "
"connector — mirroring the hierarchy in the BPMN Modeler process list."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:30
msgid ""
"Clicking a record opens it in the editor. The **+** button in the panel "
"header creates a new blank record."
msgstr ""

