#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:57
msgid ""
"The **Lookup from knowledge graph** button fires a SPARQL query against the "
"TriplyDB RONL endpoint to retrieve all `eli:LegalResource` resources linked "
"to `cpsv:PublicService` entries. Results appear as a pick-list; selecting "
"one populates both the URI and label fields automatically."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:66
msgid "Personal Data Fields tab"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:68
msgid ""
"This tab lists every personal data field collected by the forms linked to "
"this process. The **Hydrate from forms** button reads all `camunda:formRef` "
"values from the process XML, loads the matching form schemas from the Form "
"Editor storage, and appends one row per form component that has a `key` "
"property — skipping headings, text blocks, and buttons."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:75
msgid "For each field the Product Owner classifies:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:77
msgid ""
"**Data category** — `identity`, `financial`, `residence`, `health`, `civil "
"status`, `criminal`, or `other`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:78
msgid ""
"**Art. 9/10** — checkbox for health data (Art. 9) and criminal data (Art. "
"10) — renders as a red badge on the public site"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:80
msgid ""
"Non-personal fields (routing variables, computed outputs) can be removed "
"from the table using the × button on each row."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:84
msgid "BPMN Link tab"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:86
msgid ""
"The BPMN Link tab writes `ronl:ropaRef` into the process XML, formally "
"linking the record to its BPMN definition. The record must be saved first so "
"it has a UUID."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:93
msgid ""
"Clicking **Write ronl:ropaRef to BPMN** injects the attribute into the "
"process XML and saves via `BpmnService`. If the `xmlns:ronl` namespace "
"declaration is absent from the `<definitions>` element, it is added "
"automatically."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:95
msgid "The status indicator shows three states:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:97
msgid "**Not linked** — no `ronl:ropaRef` present in the XML"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:98
msgid "**Linked** (green) — `ronl:ropaRef` matches this record's ID"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:99
msgid ""
"**Points to a different record** (amber) — the XML has a `ronl:ropaRef` but "
"it references a different record ID"
msgstr ""

