#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:113
msgid ""
"Activating a record shows a confirmation dialog: *\"Activating this record "
"will make it publicly visible on ropa.flevoland.nl. Continue?\"* Status "
"changes take effect after saving the record with the **Save** button in the "
"top bar."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:117
msgid "RoPA Selector in the BPMN Modeler"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:119
msgid ""
"When a process is open in the BPMN Modeler, a **RoPA Record** panel appears "
"pinned to the bottom of the process list — below the scrollable card list. "
"It shows a dropdown of all available RoPA records and writes `ronl:ropaRef` "
"directly into the process XML on selection, without requiring any canvas "
"element to be selected."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:128
msgid "Deploy modal warning"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:130
msgid ""
"When deploying a bundle to Operaton, the deploy modal checks whether "
"`ronl:ropaRef` is present on the process element. If absent, an amber "
"warning is shown between the resource list and the resource count:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:137
msgid ""
"The warning is non-blocking — the **Deploy** button remains active. It is "
"intended to prompt the Product Owner to complete the RoPA record before "
"promoting to production."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:141
msgid "Public website"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cfeatures%5Cropa-records.md:143
msgid ""
"Active RoPA records are served from a CORS-open public endpoint and rendered "
"on a dedicated static site **[ropa.open-regels.nl]{1}** deployed separately "
"from the LDE. The site displays collapsible cards — one per record — with "
"all GDPR Art. 30 fields including the personal data fields table with colour-"
"coded data categories and Art. 9/10 flags."
msgstr ""

